  "original_title": "QR \u0d9a\u0dda\u0dad\u0dba \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Development officials away from scanning the QR code",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Association of Development Service Officers informs all development officers to withdraw from the work of checking the QR code system in fuel supply from today (15th).",
        "According to the circular sent by the Ministry of Energy to the district and divisional secretaries, the development officers were deployed to check and supervise the QR system of providing fuel for the respective categories of vehicles at the petrol stations.",
        "According to the relevant circular, the Union has informed the Minister of Power and Energy in writing on 01.08.2022 about the problems that may arise in deploying the development officers to the petrol stations for the related tasks and to solve those problems and deploy them in the relevant tasks. It is seen in a statement issued by the association that it expresses regret and strong protest.",
        "On August 10, 2022, a development officer of the Wellawaya Divisional Secretariat was attacked by an organized mob at the IOC petrol station on Monaragala Road, Wellawaya, and on August 12, 2022, a development officer of the Mirigama Divisional Secretariat, who was carrying out relevant supervisory work at the Sipetco Petrol Station, Gampaha, Mirigama, was involved in local politics. The union says that it was attacked by a thug.",
        "The officers were assaulted and their lives were threatened when the district and divisional secretaries were performing their duties as per a decision taken by the government and the responsible minister of the government who made those decisions or the heads of the institutions who ordered the implementation of the decisions did not take any reasonable steps regarding the above incident or the government The association emphasizes that not appearing on behalf of the officer is a serious situation.",
        "They say that their association paid special attention as a service to the problems faced by the development officers, although there is no professional relevance of intervening for the trade and consumer affairs of the gas stations professionally, but they intervened on the basis of providing support to avoid the inconvenience that the people were facing.",
        "Accordingly, the association further states that the development officers will withdraw from the process of monitoring the release of fuel by the fuel stations from August 15, 2022, which will be effective throughout the country from August 15, 2022."
      ],
